column4: "9 -      THE OLD HOME TOWN LOOKS THE SAME      \012"
"          AS I STEP DOWN FROM THE TRAIN        \012"
"          AND THERE TO MEET ME IS MY MAMA AND MY PAPA \012"
"          DOWN THE ROAD I LOOK AND THERE STAND MARY\011\011    \012"
"          HAIR OF GOLD AND LIPS LIKE CHERRY\012"
"          IT'S GOOD TO TOUCH THE GREEN GREEN GRASS OF HOME \012"
"25--    YES THEY ALL COME TO MEET ME\011\011\011\011\012"
"          ITS GOOD TO TOUCH THE GREEN GREEN GRASS OF HOME                     \011\012"
"33---  THE OLD HOUSE IS STILL STANDING\012"
"         THOUGH THE PAINT IS CRACKED AND DRY\012"
"         AND THERE'S THAT OLD OAK TREE THAT I USED TO PLAY ON\012"
"         DOWN THE LANE I WALK WITH MY SWEET MARY\012"
"         HAIR OF GOLD AND LIPS LIKE CHERRY\012"

column5: THE GREEN GREEN GRASS OF HOME\012"

column4: "49--- THEN I AWAKE AND LOOK AROUND ME\012"
"        AT FOUR GREY WALL THAT SURROUND ME\012"
"        AND THERE I REALIZE THAT I WAS  ONLY DREAMING\012"
"        FOR THERES A GUARD AND THERES A SAD OLD PADRE\012"
"        ARM IN ARM WE'LL WALK AND THEN AGAIN I'LL TOUCH\012"
"        THE GREEN GREEN GRASS OF HOME\012"
